    "Background": {
      "text": "Form of polymorphic\nVTach\nGradual change in the amplitude of QRS complexes and twisting around isoelectric line\nAssociated with congenital or acquired\nprolonged QT\nwhich may be secondary to medications",
      "subsections": {
        "Common_Causes": {
          "text": "POINTES\nmnemonic:\nP\nhenothiazines\nO\nther medications (ie\nTCAs\n)\nI\nntracranial bleed\nN\no known cause (idiopathic)\nT\nype I\nantiarrhythmics\n(\nquinidine\n,\nprocainamide\n, disopyramide)\nE\nlectrolyte abnormalities\n(\nhypoK\n&\nhypoMg\n)\nS\nyndrome of\nProlonged QT\n(aka Long QT Syndrome)\nOther causes:\nOrganophosphate toxicity\nHydrocarbon toxicity\nChloral hydrate toxicity\nHypothermia",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
